columns.name: # time
columns.description: This column represents the recorded time in seconds, capturing the precise moment each corresponding measurement was taken.

columns.name: velocity
columns.description: This column represents the speed of an object in motion, measured in units per second. It provides a scalar value indicating how fast the object is moving at any given point in time.

columns.name: latitude
columns.description: This column represents the geographical coordinate that specifies the north-south position of a point on the Earth's surface, measured in degrees.

columns.name: longitude
columns.description: This column represents the geographic coordinate that specifies the east-west position of a point on the Earth's surface, measured in degrees.

columns.name: angular_vel_x
columns.description: This column represents the rate of rotation around the x-axis, measured in radians per second.

columns.name: angular_vel_y
columns.description: This column represents the rate of change of angular velocity around the y-axis, measured in radians per second. It indicates how quickly an object is rotating or spinning about the vertical axis.

columns.name: angular_vel_z
columns.description: This column represents the rate of rotational motion around the z-axis, measured in radians per second. It indicates how quickly an object is spinning or rotating in the vertical plane.

columns.name: linear_acceleration_x
columns.description: This column represents the linear acceleration along the x-axis, measured in meters per second squared (m/s²). It indicates the rate of change of velocity in the horizontal direction, providing insight into the forces acting on the object in that specific axis.

columns.name: linear_acceleration_y
columns.description: This column represents the acceleration experienced along the Y-axis in a linear direction. The values are measured in units of acceleration, typically meters per second squared (m/s²), and indicate how quickly the velocity is changing along the Y-axis.

columns.name: linear_acceleration_z
columns.description: This column represents the acceleration experienced along the Z-axis, measured in meters per second squared (m/s²). It captures the rate of change of velocity in the vertical direction, providing insight into movements such as upward or downward acceleration.
